Ad Text:
About the West Region Delivery Team

The West Region Delivery Team (WRDT) is delivering one of Sydney Water’s most significant infrastructure programs, with a circa $2bn pipeline of works over 10 years.

One of our core strategic priorities is to improve how work is done, using data, automation and artificial intelligence (AI) to drive efficiency and value. This is a rare opportunity to drive and embed automation at scale across a mature and complex delivery environment.

About the opportunity

In this role you will work across the program, partnering closely with business and technical stakeholders to identify, design and implement practical automation and AI enabled solutions that reduce manual effort, streamline workflows and uplift how work is delivered. 

This is a hands-on role for someone who enjoys getting close to the work, understanding how processes really operate, and turning that insight into scalable, future-ready automation and AI use cases.

Analyse complex business processes and identify opportunities for automation and optimisation.

Partner with business SMEs to document current and future-state processes, with a strong focus on reducing manual and repetitive work.

Design, build and implement robust, reusable automation solutions.   

Work hands-on with tools such as Python, SQL, Power BI and VBA and emerging AI tools to design and deliver automation initiatives.

Conduct cost-benefit and feasibility assessments to prioritise initiatives with the greatest impact.

Develop documentation, standards and training materials to support adoption and knowledge transfer

What you’ll bring to the team

You are an experienced technical or automation analyst who thrives in complex, fast-moving environments and enjoys working at the intersection of business, data and engineering.  You’ll bring:

Strong analytical thinking and the ability to quickly understand how work actually gets done.

Hands-on experience delivering automation solutions in real business environments.

Well-developed stakeholder engagement and communication skills.

A genuine interest in automation, AI and data as drivers of business improvement.

Extensive experience in Python, VBA and/or other similar tools.

Experience with data visualisation tools such as Power BI

Experience working within construction, engineering or major infrastructure environments is highly regarded

A tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business Analytics, or equivalent practical experience.

 Why join WRDT

Work on a long-term, complex infrastructure program with real scale and impact.

Influence how automation and AI is embedded across a large and evolving digital ecosystem.

You will have end-to-end ownership, from identifying opportunities through to building and implementation.

Deliver solutions that genuinely improve efficiency, reduce cost and create value for our client

Ready to make an impact?

If this sounds like your next step, apply now or contact Hayley Urriola at hurriola@abergeldie.com for a confidential discussion.

 #bestpeople #bestdelivery #bestplanning

Pinpoint Talent is supporting a Defence client in seeking an experienced Data Observability Engineer to join a highly technical, mission-focused environment in Canberra.
This role supports Army’s digital network integration mission and plays a critical part in enabling systems-of-systems integration, test and evaluation, and experimentation across Land, Joint and Coalition capability boundaries.
  
Canberra | 12 month contract + 2x 12 month extensions | NV1 Clearance or above Mandatory
  
The position is a senior, hands-on technical role focused on the design, development, implementation, and ongoing support of data observability, monitoring, and analytics tooling. You will lead the development and maturation of data observability frameworks and processes that underpin integration testing, risk reduction, and capability validation activities. The role operates at the intersection of data engineering, communications systems engineering, networking, and DevSecOps, within a secure Defence environment.
  
You will design and integrate hardware and software solutions, review technical designs, provide systems integration advice, and support test activities, exercises, and trials. The role also includes contributing to automation and DevSecOps pipelines, producing technical documentation and reports, and providing subject matter expertise across emerging and deployed technologies.
  
Extensive experience in data observability and analytics technologies such as Elastic Stack and NetFlow, strong Linux expertise (particularly Red Hat-based systems), and hands-on experience with DevSecOps environments including CI/CD pipelines and Git-based tooling is essential.
Defence experience is essential.
  
If this sounds like you, APPLY TODAY!
Please reach out to jamie@pinpointtalent.com.au for further information.

AI Engineer (Senior)

Sydney/Melbourne

$150-200k

We are seeking a highly experienced AI Engineer with deep technical expertise and strong design thinking skills to help lead and deliver cutting-edge, practical AI solutions across a range of business use cases.

The ideal candidate will be a senior-level AI practitioner who can not only build and implement AI models and systems, but also contribute meaningfully to technical design conversations, mentor other consultants, and help shape best practices for applying AI to real-world application development.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the design, development, and deployment of AI-enabled solutions for specific business use cases, ensuring practical and scalable implementations.

Partner with cross-functional teams (front-end, back-end, and data engineering) to integrate AI capabilities into application development workflows.

Apply and extend modern AI development tools and frameworks to support high-impact projects.

Act as a technical advisor in conversations about AI system architecture, design patterns, and solution trade-offs, not limited to pure coding tasks.

Drive innovation in how AI is applied across software engineering projects, including early-stage ideation, prototyping, and production readiness.

Mentor and coach other consultants and engineers to elevate AI literacy and upskill team members.

Work across both AI engineering and software engineering domains, with a bias toward practical application development and integration.

Translate business problems into actionable AI solutions, balancing speed of delivery with maintainability and performance.

Stay current on advancements in AI technologies and tools, and help evaluate suitability for internal adoption.

Required Skills & Experience

Proven experience as a senior AI engineer or similar role with a strong delivery track record.

Deep understanding of AI/ML technologies, development tools, and frameworks.

Demonstrated experience with both the design and implementation of AI systems in production contexts.

Strong coding skills in languages such as Python, with experience applying AI and ML libraries.

Ability to engage in solution design discussions and make sound technical recommendations.

Experience with software engineering practices, including collaboration with front-end, back-end, and data engineering teams.

A mindset geared toward practical, use-case driven AI delivery rather than theoretical research.

Strong mentoring, communication, and knowledge-sharing capabilities.

Familiarity with modern AI development tooling (e.g., model hubs, generative AI SDKs, LLM APIs, MLOps tooling).

Nice to Have

Experience upskilling technical teams or running internal enablement initiatives.

Background in data engineering or systems integration.

Exposure to cloud-native deployment of AI applications.

Prior consulting experience where translation between business needs and technical execution was central.

Why This Role Matters

This role will be central to accelerating how AI capabilities are designed and delivered across meaningful business solutions. Beyond building models, the successful candidate will influence how teams think about AI engineering, help raise the overall technical capability of the organisation, and ensure AI is applied in ways that generate real value.

We are partnering with a leading Australian Automation and robotics organisation that have been providing smart solutions to the food, industrial and beverage production sectors for over 50 years. 

Working as the Software Engineer you will play a key role in delivering data-driven solutions for industrial automation projects within the fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) sector. This position requires expertise in integrating OT (Operational Technology) and IT systems, developing scalable software solutions, and ensuring seamless connectivity between plant-floor equipment and enterprise-level systems. The role will involve working at our Seven Hills facility as well as customer sites, which may include occasional weekends and public holidays to support project delivery and commissioning activities.

The role involves:

Design & development of solutions and databases
Integration of PLC's, MES and SCADA systems
Write code for Rockwell Automation, Siemens & TIA portals
Enable real time data gathering and analysis
To be successful in this role you will possess;

Strong background in industrial Automation
Database design and SQL query
PLC programming (Rockwell / Siemens) 
C# & Python for custom applications

If you are an electronics / mechatronics / software engineer with experience and an interest in Automation and robotics then we would love to hear from you. Please click on the Apply now button and we will reply within 48 business hours

We’re seeking an AI Engineering Lead to join Virgin Australia Group at a pivotal time in their transformation. This role is for a technically strong leader who leads from the front, setting direction, staying hands on, and building high-performing teams that deliver real business impact.

In this role, you’ll bridge deep technical execution with business outcomes, ensuring the AI engineering team delivers high-quality, scalable solutions that support Virgin Australia’s ambition to be the most loved airline.

Your day-to-day will include:
Leading a team of AI engineers, providing technical guidance, mentorship, and clear engineering standards
Owning architectural decisions and ensuring solutions are robust, secure, and fit for long-term use
Staying hands-on where needed to unblock delivery and model best-practice engineering
Partnering closely with senior stakeholders to translate complex technical concepts into clear business outcomes
Driving consistent engineering practices across code quality, testing, deployment, and operational excellence
Identifying and mitigating technical risks before they impact delivery or system reliability
Contributing to broader cross-team technical discussions to share knowledge and improve consistency across the engineering organisation
About You: You’re an experienced AI engineering leader who enjoys solving complex problems and developing people as much as technology. Ideally, you’ll bring:

Proven experience designing, building, and operating AI production-grade systems in complex environments
Demonstrated success leading engineering teams, including mentoring, delivery ownership, and technical decision-making
A strong technical foundation in your area of expertise, with the ability to evaluate emerging tools and trends
Confidence communicating technical trade-offs, timelines, and risks to both technical and non-technical stakeholders
A pragmatic approach to balancing delivery speed with code quality and manageable technical debt
A collaborative mindset and a genuine interest in building high-performing, engaged teams
If you’re passionate about shaping AI platforms, leading talented engineers, and playing a key role in a large-scale, customer-focused organisation, this role offers both challenge and influence in equal measure.
  
If you are seeking your next position and would like to discuss this opportunity in further and expanded detail, please reach out directly to Dan Nyhuis at daniel.nyhuis@troocoo.com

Data Observability Engineer (NV1) – Secure Analytics & Monitoring

Join a hands-on engineering team building and maturing data observability and analytics capabilities across complex, secure environments. You’ll design, implement and support monitoring/analytics tooling (think Elastic/ELK and NetFlow), automate repeatable processes, and contribute to technical documentation and integration outcomes for a high-impact program.


Location: Canberra, ACT (Onsite – Symonston)

Contract Duration: March 2026 to 30 October 2027 + two (2) x 12-month extension options
Security Clearance: Must hold a current NV1 (or higher) clearance
Closing Date: 10:00am Friday 13 February 2026

Essential Tasks:

Design, build and implement data observability and analytics tooling (Elastic/ELK, NetFlow).
Develop and maintain observability practices/procedures, including root cause analysis and optimisation advice.
Collaborate with engineering and validation teams to deploy/maintain experimental systems and support architectural decisions.
Provide SME support, reporting, and technical uplift (including just-in-time training as required).

Key Criteria:

Strong data observability/analytics experience (Elastic/ELK, Elastic Stack, NetFlow).
Advanced Linux capability (Red Hat environments) plus automation/scripting (e.g., Python/Bash/PowerShell).
DevSecOps and integration experience (CI/CD e.g., GitLab, APIs, networking/virtualisation).

How to Apply

Does this role sound perfect for you? If so, to register your interest in this role, please either contact Peter Ding or the Compas Team on (02) 6230 0233 and send through your CV by following the link below.


About Compas:

Compas Pty Ltd is a Canberra based wholly Australian owned, Recruitment and Services company that has been operating since 1987. We specialise in the provision of permanent, contract and temporary recruitment services, as well as specialised Consulting assignments.


YOUR APPLICATION WILL BE TREATED WITH THE STRICTEST CONFIDENCE

Due to the nature of this environment, candidates must hold a current NV1 clearance.

What success looks like in this role:

We are seeking a highly experienced Microsoft 365 Consultant/Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will possess extensive experience in Microsoft 365 implementation, configuration, and migration projects. This role requires exceptional technical skills, strong communication abilities, and a solid understanding of both on-premises and cloud-based infrastructure.

Key Responsibilities

Work with Architect and execute Microsoft 365 implementation and migration projects, ensuring minimal disruption to business operations.

Implement comprehensive Microsoft 365 solutions tailored to client needs, encompassing various workloads including Exchange Online, SharePoint Online, OneDrive for Business, Teams, Teams Voice, Active Directory, and Entra ID.

Provide expert IT consulting services, guiding clients through the design and implementation phases of Microsoft 365 projects.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate Microsoft 365 solutions with existing on-premises infrastructure, such as Active Directory, servers, network, EUC, and applications.

Utilize PowerShell scripting to automate administrative tasks and enhance the efficiency of Microsoft 365 implementations.

Maintain up-to-date knowledge of Microsoft 365 technologies, industry trends, and best practices to ensure the delivery of cutting-edge solutions.

Identify and troubleshoot technical issues related to Microsoft 365 environments, providing timely resolutions to maintain optimal system performance.

Communicate effectively with clients, stakeholders, and team members to ensure the successful delivery of projects and fulfillment of client requirements.


Required Skills and Experience

Proven experience in delivering complex Microsoft 365 projects.

Expertise in Microsoft 365 implementation, configuration, and migration.

Strong technical skills across various Microsoft 365 workloads, including:

Exchange Online

SharePoint Online

OneDrive for Business

Teams

Teams Voice

Extensive knowledge of on-premises infrastructure, including Active Directory, servers, networks, EUC, and applications.

Proficiency in PowerShell scripting for automation and administrative tasks.

Excellent communication skills, with the ability to convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Strong troubleshooting skills and a methodical approach to problem-solving.

Ability to work independently and as part of a team, managing multiple priorities and deadlines.


You will be successful in this role if you have:

NV1 Security Clerance is required.

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

Strong problem-solving and analytical abilities.

Familiarity with industry best practices and regulatory requirements related to Microsoft 365 and cloud-based solutions.

Ad Text:
Talent International, a leading Australian recruitment firm, have been engaged by our long standing client, an international Music and Entertainment organisation. We are seeking a Principal Engineer - AI and Automation, to pioneer AI and Automation across their global technology function.

This is a rare opportunity to shape strategy, drive meaningful change, and build AI capability from the ground up with real executive visibility.

Role Title: Principal Engineer - AI and Automation

Opportunity: Permanent Career Opportunity

Location: Sydney CBD

Salary: $220,000 incl super + 15% annual bonus

Client Industry: Music and Entertainment

Start Date: ASAP

Interview Process: 3 rounds of interviews

Role Details:


Own and execute the enterprise AI and automation strategy for Technology Operations, aligning initiatives to business outcomes and long-term platform maturity.
Architect, build, and govern end-to-end AI-driven (agentic) automation solutions, taking concepts from ideation through production, adoption, and continuous optimisation.
Identify, evaluate, and prioritise high-impact use cases where AI can materially reduce operational complexity, accelerate incident response, and deliver measurable efficiency and reliability gains.
Partner with senior technology leaders and delivery teams to embed AI and automation into core platforms and operational workflows, ensuring sustained adoption, value realisation, and scalability.
Provide technical leadership and oversight across AI and automation initiatives, including vendor strategy, platform selection, and architectural standards, within a complex, global environment.

Required Skills and Experiences:

10+ years of experience in the IT operations industry
Demonstrated experience designing or delivering AI-driven, Machine Learning or intelligent automation solutions, with a focus on real-world adoption and outcomes
Ability to operate at a senior, principal level with a consultative approach, confidently influencing fellow leaders and stakeholders and driving adoption across global teams
Familiarity with cloud platforms such as Amazon Web Service, Azure, and Google Cloud.
Experience with automation tools such as Automation Anywhere, UiPath, Zapier, Microsoft Power Automate, and ActiveCampaign.

Additional Details & Benefits:

Working from home flexibility
Annual bonus
Team Events and Activities
Opportunity to join a new, global team

To Apply:

If this sounds like your next opportunity or you would like to hear more, please 'apply now' and submit your resume!


For more information or a confidential discussion please contact Sienna Coate Thompson at Talent International - Sienna.coatethompson@talentinternational.com

Senior AI Engineer

Location Sydney (hybrid)
Team: AI Squad | IT
Reporting to: Group Manager – Data & AI

The opportunity: 
We’re looking for a Senior AI Engineer to design, build, and operate production-grade AI systems that deliver measurable business value. This role sits at the intersection of engineering excellence, applied AI, and real-world outcomes — not experiments for experiment’s sake.

You’ll work on modern AI solutions including LLMs, RAG, agents, and ML services, deployed at scale on Azure and Databricks, with strong governance, security, and operational discipline.

What you’ll be doing

Build and deploy AI services and APIs for inference and retrieval (LLMs, RAG, ML models, agents)
Develop data pipelines for training and retrieval with strong governance, privacy, and auditability
Contribute to the AI platform and MLOps toolchain (CI/CD for models, MLflow, feature stores, monitoring, rollback)
Translate business and product requirements into well-scoped technical deliverables
Write clean, well-tested code and contribute reusable components and patterns
Operate AI workloads in production with clear SLIs/SLOs (availability, latency, cost)
Apply security-by-design practices including prompt protection, content filtering, access controls
Maintain documentation, runbooks, and architectural decision records
What we’re looking for

Advanced engineering in Python and microservices, with expertise in cloud-native architecture on Azure.
Hands-on with Databricks (Delta, Unity Catalog, MLflow) and Azure OpenAI / Azure ML
Solid understanding of RAG patterns, tools/agents, and function calling
Strong data engineering fundamentals (batch & streaming pipelines, data quality, lineage)
Practical experience securing AI systems (privacy, prompt safety, auditability)
Ability to turn real customer problems into working AI solutions
Comfortable working in cross-functional teams and owning outcomes end-to-end
Nice to have

Azure, Databricks, or related certifications
Experience operating AI at enterprise scale
Background in regulated or data-sensitive environments
Why this role
Work on real, production AI in an enterprise environment — not demos
Strong focus on engineering quality, security, and operational excellence
Influence platform standards and reusable AI patterns
Clear connection between your work and business impact

Curious to know more? Apply today for a confidential discussion. We look forward to connecting with you

Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, drive performance management, and develop high-performing teams. Powered by people science and the most comprehensive employee dataset in the world, the most innovative companies including Canva, On, Asana, Dolby, McDonalds and Nasdaq depend on Culture Amp every day.

Culture Amp is backed by leading venture capital funds and has offices in the US, UK, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp has been recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and most innovative companies by Fast Company.

For more information visit cultureamp.com.

How you can help make a better world of work

We're looking for a Senior Engineer to join the AI Research & Experience team, helping build AI Coach - Culture Amp's contextually-aware AI system that integrates survey insights, performance management, and interpersonal dynamics to deliver personalized support to organizations, teams, and individuals at scale.

You'll work at the intersection of applied AI research and product engineering, translating cutting-edge techniques into production systems that genuinely improve how people experience work. This isn't a research lab - you'll be shipping features that solve real customer problems. 

What you'll do

Staying up to date with current research, literature and provider offerings. 
Design, implement and evaluate areas and features of our multi-agentic platform and systems using modern frameworks (e.g., LangGraph) for stateful, multi-turn coaching conversations.
Advise, help build, and orchestrate data pipelines that unify fragmented workplace data (surveys, goals, performance reviews, feedback, 1-1 notes) into coherent coaching context
Translate customer requirements into technical solutions - working backwards from user needs to system design. Creating technical documentation to support literacy, technical transfer and engineering practice.
Partner closely with product, design, and people science to ensure the features developed are fit for purpose, and in-line with the existing product expectations to ensure seamless partnership transfer of technology.
Contribute to evaluation frameworks and bias testing to meet enterprise requirements for transparency and fairness
Build cutting-edge, working prototypes, integrated into our environments which validate new approaches and accelerate learning.
What we're looking for


Must Haves:

Proven commercial experience taking ML/AI systems to production.
Strong technical writer and communicator
Full stack software development experience, ideally Python, React, PGVector
Strong software engineering fundamentals - you write clean, tested, maintainable code. 
You leverage Software development AI tooling effectively.
Experience with LLM application development (prompt and context engineering, RAG, agent architectures)
Hands-on experience designing and integrating data pipelines - you're comfortable moving data across systems, working within rigorous security standards, handling messy real-world inputs, and building robust orchestration
A pragmatic, solution-focused mindset - you evaluate new technology through the lens of "does this scalably solve the problem?" not "is this technically interesting?"
You fit our values with the proactivity to take risks, and the humility to learn in public. You take pride in your work and its successful utilisation, stability, extendability and maintainability. 

Strong signals:

Experience at startups or founding teams - comfortable with ambiguity and fast iteration
Postgraduate degree (Masters or PhD) in Machine Learning, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, or related quantitative field
Evidence of taking cutting-edge (relevant) techniques from paper to production
Experience with evaluation/benchmarking frameworks for AI systems
Experience integrating scalable solutions such as advanced Speech-to-Text (STT) and Text-to-Speech (TTS) pipelines (e.g., Whisper, ElevenLabs) with streaming capabilities
Experience implementing GraphRAG or Knowledge Graphs (e.g., Neo4j)

Bonus:

Familiarity with people analytics, HR tech, or behavioral science applications
Contributions to data ethics, algorithmic fairness, or responsible AI initiatives
Open source contributions or public technical writing
Why join AIRX


You'll work at scale on hard problems that matter - building AI that helps organizations develop their people, improve feedback culture, and foster the conditions for sustainable high performance. Our approach is deeply informed by Culture Amp's people science research. You'll be surrounded by talented and passionate advocates for humanity and cutting edge AI in the world of work.

We believe that our employees are the heartbeat of our success. We're committed to fostering a work environment that truly cares for and develops its people, and creates lasting positive impact. In addition to providing a competitive compensation package, some of the key benefits we offer are: 

Employee Share Options Program: We empower you to be an owner in Culture Amp and share in our success
Programs, coaching, and budgets to help you thrive personally and professionally
Access to external providers for mental wellbeing and coaching support to sustain the wellbeing, safety and development of our people
Monthly Camper Life Allowance: An automatic allowance paid out each month with your pay - you can spend it however you like to help improve your experience and life outside work
Team budgets dedicated to team building activities and connection
Intentional quarterly wellbeing pauses: A quarterly company-wide shutdown day in each region to to collectively pause, reset and focus on restoration and rest, without having to tap into individual vacation time
Extended year-end breaks: An extended refresh period at the end of year
Excellent parental leave and in work support program available from day 1 of joining Culture Amp
5 Social Impact Days a year to make a positive impact on the community outside of work
MacBooks for you to do your best & a work from home office budget to spend on setting up your home office
Medical insurance coverage for you and your family (Available for US & UK only) 

Additionally, we don't just focus on our internal community; we believe in creating a better world of work for all. We're committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion, with Employee Resource Groups and ally communities in place. 

We have a strong commitment to Anti-Racism, and endeavor to lead by example. Every step we make as a business towards anti-racism is another step we can take to support our customers in making a better world (of work). You can see our current commitments to Anti-Racism here.

Overview

Do you enjoy solving problems, looking at problems through a different lens, and working closely with customers to innovate new solutions to complex problems? Do you jump with excitement at the opportunity to identify trends and provide unique business solutions? Do you want to join a team where learning about a new technology or solution is part of our work every day? 

The Industry Solutions Delivery (ISD) Engineering & Architecture Group (EAG) is a global consulting and engineering organization that supports our most complex and leading-edge customer engagements.  Driving early-stage deliveries, enhances ISD’s technical capabilities, and partnering with others to develop approaches, innovative solutions, and engineering standards in order to set our sales and delivery teams up for success.  We provide consistent high-quality customer experience through technical and AI leadership and IP capture centred on delivery truth. 

Responsibilities

Engage stakeholders to understand business drivers and confidently communicate insights, recommendations, and tradeoffs 

Partner with customers to translate complex business problems into data science solutions with clear objectives, assumptions, risks, and success criteria 

Work closely with Solution Architects, Consultants, and Data Engineers who will source and prepare data from multiple systems. 

Explore and evaluate data quality, integrity, and fitness for purpose, clearly explaining implications to customers.  

Design and deliver machine learning solutions covering Generative AI, Agentic solutions, computer vision, speech processing,  forecasting, NLP, classification, clustering, reinforcement learning and optimization.  

Frame the problem appropriately; and select and apply appropriate algorithms, modelling techniques, and experimental methods to meet client and project requirements  

Conduct statistical analysis and controlled experiments, translating findings into measurable business outcomes  

Support model testing and validation using test and production data, incorporating customer feedback into improvements  

Collaborate with engineering teams to deploy scalable, secure, and reliable models into customer environments  

Manage customer expectations on scope, timelines, and outcomes, contributing to strong delivery experiences  

Stay current with industry trends and contribute to thought leadership and reusable intellectual property 

Qualifications

Required/Minimum Qualifications 

Master’s degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or a related field and 7+ years of professional data science experience 
or 

Doctorate in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or a related field and 4+ years of professional data science experience 
or 

Equivalent practical experience demonstrated through long-term, hands-on delivery of data science solutions 

Strong foundation in data science principles, including statistics, machine learning, and analytical modelling 

Proven problem-solving skills with the ability to break down complex business and technical challenges 

Handson experience developing and deploying machine learning and advanced AI solutions to production environments on public cloud platforms 

Professional experience working with Generative AI solutions in production environments (beyond pilots or POC /proof of concepts) 

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Job Title: Senior Systems Engineer - MQ-28 Payloads Engineering
Ad Text:
The Boeing MQ-28 Ghost Bat is a globally-significant program that will deliver a disruptive advantage to support Defence operational capabilities. Developed in partnership with the Royal Australian Air Force, it is the first military combat aircraft to be designed, manufactured and assembled in Australia in 50 years. 

As we continue to mature the platform and rapidly expand on its skills and capabilities, Boeing Defence Australia (BDA) are seeking an experienced Systems Engineer to support the design, development, integration and testing of new capability for the MQ-28 Ghost Bat. You will work collaboratively across an interdisciplinary and multinational team on cutting edge systems. 

This role is based in Brisbane and reports into the MQ-28 Payloads Engineering Manager. 

As an experienced Senior Systems Engineer you will:

Engage and collaborate with key internal and external stakeholders across technical engineering and specialty areas to develop and integrate innovative solutions to achieve capability objectives and requirements of the MQ-28 Mission System.
Apply an interdisciplinary, collaborative approach to requirements development and management including analysis of functional and non-functional requirements, functional performance specifications, architecture and interfaces to develop effective solutions for complex systems.
Manage dependencies, assess trades and conduct technical design reviews in collaboration with the broader project team to ensure the engineering scope is delivered with quality and on schedule.
Lead and develop verification requirements, test plans, procedures and reports.
Coordinate, plan and conduct integration and formal verification testing of the MQ-28 Mission System.
Support ground and flight test operations for the MQ-28 Mission System.
Demonstrate leadership in development, review and approval of engineering documentation and designs while providing mentoring of less experienced staff.
Manage technical risk and support identification, analysis and resolution of problem reports.
Plan and coordinate incremental capability development and delivery within an AGILE framework. 

To be considered for the role you will have:

Minimum of 5 years' experience in complex technical development and integration projects
Hold Tertiary qualifications in either Aerospace, Avionics, Electrical or Mechatronics Engineering or equivalent technical experience in a Systems Engineering discipline.
Demonstrated experience in systems and software development lifecycle (essential).
Demonstrated experience in avionics system level testing in a laboratory and ground test environments (desirable).
Experience with aircraft avionics, sensors and UAV systems (desirable).
Familiarity with engineering change processes.
Familiarity with software development, test and integration.
Experience with aerospace and / or Defence projects (highly regarded). 

Applicants must be Australian Citizens to meet Defence security requirements. 

What's on offer?

Boeing values the health and wellbeing of our employees and offer true flexibility including working from home, compressed work weeks, and opportunities for part time arrangements, allowing you to balance your career with what is important to you outside of work.

Other benefits:

Work on cutting edge projects with opportunities to work across platforms.
Attractive remuneration and annual bonus.
Formal mentoring and training as well as on the job learning.
Formal reward and recognition program.
Access discounts for health insurance, travel and accommodation.
Paid study leave, paid parental leave and Defence leave.
Salary packaging options available.
Health and wellbeing benefits including annual flu vaccinations and Employee Assistance Program.
Social and community groups. 

BDA works with strong links with our global Boeing community and we strongly encourage collaboration with our international counterparts. 

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace. Female applicants, people of Aboriginal or Torres Strait Island descent and veterans are encouraged to apply. 

If you are ready to join an innovative industry leader and would like to register your interest in working for Boeing, please click Apply Now.

Design, develop, and operate backend systems that power blockchain analytics, attribution, and risk intelligence products
